Why Postorder?
int left = height(root->left);
int right = height(root->right);

Before processing current node, you first process:

Left subtree
Right subtree
Then current node

which is exactly:
= Postorder DFS

CODE-->
class Solution {
public:
    int diameter = 0;
    int height(TreeNode*root){
        if(root == NULL)
        return 0;

        int left = height(root->left);
        int right = height(root->right);

        diameter = max(diameter, left + right);
        return 1 + max(left,right);
    }
    int diameterOfBinaryTree(TreeNode* root) {
        height(root);
        return diameter;
    }
};
At every node, ask:

How many nodes can I go down on the left?
How many nodes can I go down on the right?
